{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Future local tuning and continuous learning AI algorithmsLocal tuning of AI models and continuous-learning AI algorithms prior to deployment have theoretical potential to improve the local performance of AI products.",
    "However, to date all AI tools which have received regulatory approval are static and cannot be locally tuned or undergo modifications using adaptive learning techniques.",
    "Recently, the US Food and Drug Administration (FDA) has released draft guidance for a \"Predetermined Change Control Plan\" [84] that would allow future modification to commercial algorithms for both local tuning and continuous learning.",
    "Any change control plan must include robust real-time AI model performance and measures that mitigate patient risk.",
    "Currently, this guidance has not been implemented but would be for models that are in the process of obtaining approval rather than those already approved."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Recently, the US Food and Drug Administration (FDA) has released draft guidance for a \"Predetermined Change Control Plan\" [84] that would allow future modification to commercial algorithms for both local tuning and continuous learning."
  ]
}